  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will follow 2500 prevalent Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) patients with Glomerular
      Filtration Rate (GFR) from 15-45 ml/min for 30 months with serial measurements every 6 months
      and subsequent annual chart review up to 60 months. This observational study will analyze the
      demographics, clinical status, medications and blood and urine samples of these patients and
      study the conventional biochemical, hormonal and metabolic parameters assessing which
      underlying biomarkers reflect the processes involved with disease progression.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
